{"lemma":"قُبَّةٌ","slug":"قُبَّةٌ","root":"ق.ب.ب","root_slug":"ق-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35031"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"canopy, pavilion; dome, cupola"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kippah, yarmulke (Jewish head covering)","tags":["Judaism"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic קוּבְּתָא / ܩܘܼܒ݁ܬ݂ܵܐ (qubbəṯā)."},"ipa":["/qub.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35031","headword_ar":"قُبَّةٌ","root":"qb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of structure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, O, Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb, TA;) and applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a round"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayot","text_ar":"بَيْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pavilion"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known among the Turkumán and the Akrád;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaroqaAhap","text_ar":"خَرْقَاهَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[an Arabicized word from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xarokaAh","text_ar":"خَرْكَاه"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Mgh, Msb;) and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any round structure:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a structure of skins,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tanned hides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"peculiarly; (M, TA;) derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~a Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"قَبَّ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~abahu","text_ar":"قَبَّبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ he collected, or gathered together, the extremities of the thing: ” (M:) accord. to IAth, it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small round tent of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaA='","text_ar":"خِبَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the tents of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the 'Ináyeh it is said to be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is raised for the purpose of the entering thereinto;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and not to be peculiarly a structure: (TA:) [also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dome-like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent-like, covering"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman's camel-vehicle of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawodaj","text_ar":"هَوْدَج"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cupola, of stone"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bricks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a building covered with a dome"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cupola:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibaAbN","text_ar":"قِبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qubabN","text_ar":"قُبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, O, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~apu Als~anaAmi","text_ar":"قُبَّةُ السَّنَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The round, protuberant, upper portion of the camel's hump"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaHadapN","text_ar":"قَحَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~apu AlA_isolaAmi","text_ar":"قُبَّةُ الاـِسْلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an appellation of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"El-Basrah."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqub~apu","text_ar":"القُبَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the name by which some of the Arabs call (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thirteen stars that compose the constellation of Corona Australis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of their round form. (Kzw.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","O","Msb","TA","Mgh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}